Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}(minced). Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Tunisian Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, half the @Yogurt{2%tbsp}, half the garlic, 1 TBSP @Olive Oil{}, a squeeze of lemon juice, 1 tsp @Salt{1%tsp}, and @Pepper{}. Add chicken and turn to coat. Set aside to marinate.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil and 2 tsp salt.

== Roasted Carrots ==

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Roughly chop @Pistachios{1/2%oz}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%oz}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, @Salt{}, and a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%tsp}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{25%minutes}.

== Garlic Sauce ==

While carrots roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{2%tbsp} and remaining yogurt with garlic to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @Water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium heat.

Remove chicken from marinade; allow excess to drip off. Add chicken to pan and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side.

> Cooking over medium heat helps prevent the marinade from burning. Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Once cool enough to handle, slice chicken crosswise.

== Pistachio Couscous ==

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add pistachios and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter.

Add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%cup} and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring, until toasted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @Water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest and half the cilantro. Season with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use 1 1/2 cups water.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, couscous, and carrots between plates. Drizzle chicken with garlic sauce and sprinkle with remaining cilantro and with chili flakes if desired. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.